abstract: In the pre-dawn hours of Nov. 28, after Iraqi demonstrators set the Iranian consulate in the southern holy city of Najaf ablaze, the killings began.
snippet: In the pre-dawn hours of Nov. 28, after Iraqi demonstrators set the Iranian consulate in the southern holy city of Najaf ablaze, the killings began.
lead_paragraph: NAJAF, Iraq — In the pre-dawn hours of Nov. 28, after Iraqi demonstrators set the Iranian consulate in the southern holy city of Najaf ablaze, the killings began.
headline_main: How One Deadly Day Prompted Iraqi Leader's Exit
headline_print_headline: How One Deadly Day Prompted Iraqi Leader's Exit

abstract: The Trump administration on Monday slapped sanctions on two South Sudanese officials accused of undermining peace efforts in the African nation.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration on Monday slapped sanctions on two South Sudanese officials accused of undermining peace efforts in the African nation.
headline_main: US Hits 2 More South Sudanese Officials With Sanctions

abstract: Estonia apologized to Finland on Monday after Estonia's interior minister mocked Finland's new prime minister -- the world's youngest-serving government leader -- as "a sales girl" and questioned her ability to run the Nordic country.
snippet: Estonia apologized to Finland on Monday after Estonia's interior minister mocked Finland's new prime minister -- the world's youngest-serving government leader -- as "a sales girl" and questioned her ability to run the Nordic country.
lead_paragraph: HELSINKI/TALLINN — Estonia apologized to Finland on Monday after Estonia's interior minister mocked Finland's new prime minister -- the world's youngest-serving government leader -- as "a sales girl" and questioned her ability to run the Nordic country.
headline_main: Estonia Apologizes After Minister Taunts Finnish PM as 'Sales Girl'
headline_print_headline: Estonia Apologizes After Minister Taunts Finnish PM as 'Sales Girl'

abstract: We can’t excuse an abuse of power just because it supports our side.
snippet: We can’t excuse an abuse of power just because it supports our side.
lead_paragraph: Last week, the House Judiciary Committee debated articles of impeachment drawn from a densely argued, sharply worded 300-page report that the Democratic majority on the House Intelligence Committee produced. It is an investigative tour de force, written for posterity. In considerable detail, using interviews and records, it describes, for example, how President Trump’s top personal adviser, Rudolph W. Giuliani, traipsed across Europe, circumventing diplomats as he furthered the president’s direct political interests. It also delves into the circumstances behind Mr. Giuliani’s repeated contacts with a reporter, John Solomon of The Hill, and marshals a case that Mr. Solomon’s reporting helped push a false and damaging narrative about the then-serving American ambassador to Ukraine, Marie Yovanovitch.

abstract: The federal government’s 2.1 million employees will get paid parental leave for the first time, a galvanizing moment in the growing movement to bring the benefit to all U.S. workers.
snippet: The federal government’s 2.1 million employees will get paid parental leave for the first time, a galvanizing moment in the growing movement to bring the benefit to all U.S. workers.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The federal government’s 2.1 million employees will get paid parental leave for the first time, a galvanizing moment in the growing movement to bring the benefit to all U.S. workers.
headline_main: Paid Parental Leave for Fed Workers Could Spur Wider Changes
headline_print_headline: Paid Parental Leave for Fed Workers Could Spur Wider Changes

abstract: A leading Polish newspaper on Monday welcomed a ruling in favor of one its journalists, who was taken to court by the populist ruling party over an ironic tweet that referred to “mafia” elements within the party.
snippet: A leading Polish newspaper on Monday welcomed a ruling in favor of one its journalists, who was taken to court by the populist ruling party over an ironic tweet that referred to “mafia” elements within the party.
lead_paragraph: WARSAW, Poland — A leading Polish newspaper on Monday welcomed a ruling in favor of one its journalists, who was taken to court by the populist ruling party over an ironic tweet that referred to “mafia” elements within the party.
headline_main: Polish Newspaper, Sued Repeatedly by Ruling Party, Wins Case
headline_print_headline: Polish Newspaper, Sued Repeatedly by Ruling Party, Wins Case

abstract: Outraged concert-goers shouting "revolution, revolution" hounded former Lebanese prime minister Fouad Siniora from a Christmas concert at the American University of Beirut on Sunday night.
snippet: Outraged concert-goers shouting "revolution, revolution" hounded former Lebanese prime minister Fouad Siniora from a Christmas concert at the American University of Beirut on Sunday night.
lead_paragraph: BEIRUT — Outraged concert-goers shouting "revolution, revolution" hounded former Lebanese prime minister Fouad Siniora from a Christmas concert at the American University of Beirut on Sunday night.
headline_main: Spontaneous Protest Hounds Former Lebanese PM From Concert
headline_print_headline: Spontaneous Protest Hounds Former Lebanese PM From Concert
